<subSubSection id="C3683DCCA778FF91FF5DFB0D31565BAB" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BCD6E47A778FF91FF5DFB0D31565BAB" blockId="33.[151,1437,153,1260]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="B906B255A778FF91FF5DFB0D35975BE4" bold="true" box="[199,494,1160,1187]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Distribution and habitat.</emphasis>
This species is known only from 
<collectingCountry id="F3652ED7A778FF91FCF1FB0C37B05BE4" box="[875,969,1161,1187]" name="Namibia" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Namibia</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="134972C2A778FF91FC40FB0C30455BE4" box="[986,1084,1160,1187]" captionStart="FIGURES 153–154" captionStartId="71.[151,264,1983,2008]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,179,1929]" captionTargetId="figure@71.[174,1414,179,1955]" captionTargetPageId="71" captionText="FIGURES 153–154. Distribution maps of Afroptera spp." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335180/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 154</figureCitation>
). The range of distribution falls within the Nama Karoo Biome’s extension into southern 
<collectingCountry id="F3652ED7A778FF91FC9CFB2837115B80" box="[774,872,1197,1223]" name="Namibia" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Namibia</collectingCountry>
. The habitat is dry, vegetated mostly by low shrubs, grasses, succulents and annual forbs. It receives predominantly summer rains (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE313B6A778FF91FC6AFB54315A5BAB" author="Mucina, L. &amp; Rutherford, M. C." box="[1008,1315,1233,1260]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="1 - 808" refId="ref48773" refString="Mucina, L. &amp; Rutherford, M. C. (2006) The vegetation of South Africa, Lesotho and Swaziland. In: Strelitzia. Vol. 19. South African National Biodiversity Institute, Pretoria, pp. 1 - 808." type="book chapter" year="2006">Mucina &amp; Rutherford 2006</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
